07/09/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The leader of the ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD), Prime Minister Adrian Nastase, won the PSD primary held Sunday (5 September) to determine candidates in the November general elections. According to the party, Nastase won the majority of votes in the race for Chamber of Deputies candidates, while Sorin Oprescu came in first on the Senate list. (Mediafax, Nine o'clock - 06/09/04)
